We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. Of the options given, only LDH is typically elevated in dysgerminoma, which is a type of ovarian germ cell tumor. LDH is not specific for ovarian germ cell tumors, but it can be used to monitor treatment response and detect recurrence. Beta-hCG and AFP are markers for non-germ cell ovarian tumors, while CA-125 is a marker for epithelial ovarian tumors.

Beta-human chorionic gonadotropin (beta-hCG) is elevated in some other germ cell tumors such as choriocarcinoma, but not in dysgerminoma. Alpha-fetoprotein (AFP) is elevated in non-seminomatous germ cell tumors and hepatocellular carcinoma, but not in dysgerminoma. Cancer antigen 125 (CA-125) is typically elevated in ovarian epithelial tumors, not germ cell tumors such as dysgerminoma.
